text.390:
Velasco: Ramon Ang is our ninong (godfather) in our wedding but I am friends with other tycoons as well.

Yes, I have already talked to Enrique Razon. It was just a friendly conversation... As you know, I am a former NUP member. | via @JCGotinga
text.391: Velasco says he will support Sara Duterte if she runs for President, and that he has asked her many times to run. | via @JCGotinga
text.392:
Velasco: I always have dinner with [Davao City] Mayor Sara Duterte. That dinner (the one in photo) was me asking for the endorsement of her party, the Hugpong ng Pagbabago.

I agree, her support was the tipping point. | via @JCGotinga
text.393: Velasco: Cayetano apologized to the President and to me. He said he was sorry for what happened. He kept on saying that he might have misread the instructions of the President. | via @JCGotinga
text.394:
Velasco says he is offering former speaker Alan Peter Cayetano a deputy speaker post as a sign of respect, and he would want to meet with his predecessor.

There was no promise made that Taguig City's budget won't be touched, Velasco says. | via @JCGotinga
text.395: Velasco: Yes, definitely I will give former Minority Leader Benny Abante a post. (What post?) It's still under evaluation. | via @JCGotinga
text.396:
